	<Title>
		Recipe: Red, white and blue parfait
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Red, white and blue parfait &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip" />
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Make creamy filling by placing yogurt, cream cheese and honey into bowl and beating until fluffy. Assembly parfaits by placing 1/3 cup strawberries in each parfait glass. Top each with 3 tablespoons of creamy filling, then 1/4 cup blueberries. Garnish each by dividing remaining topping. Chill until ready to serve.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 pint fresh strawberries, sliced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cups fresh blueberries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Creamy filling 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 cup low-fat, artificially sweetened vanilla yogurt&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup fat-free cream cheese, softened&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 teaspoon honey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
